Story: read the 'node add' help message
  As a cluster administrator
  I want to read help message of 'node add'
  So that I can understand how to add a node to the system

  Scenario: node help add
    When I run ./node help add
    Then the first line of the help message should be a usage example
    And the help message should include a description of -i and --installer option
    And the help message should include a description of -a and --address option
    And the help message should include a description of -n and --netmask option
    And the help message should include a description of -g and --gateway option
    And the help message should include a description of -m and --mac option
    And the help message should include a description of -w and --wol option
    And the help message should include a description of -t and --trace option
    And the help message should include a description of -v and --verbose option
    And the help message should include a description of -h and --help option

  Scenario: node add --help
    When I run ./node add --help
    Then the first line of the help message should be a usage example
    And the help message should include a description of -i and --installer option
    And the help message should include a description of -a and --address option
    And the help message should include a description of -n and --netmask option
    And the help message should include a description of -g and --gateway option
    And the help message should include a description of -m and --mac option
    And the help message should include a description of -w and --wol option
    And the help message should include a description of -t and --trace option
    And the help message should include a description of -v and --verbose option
    And the help message should include a description of -h and --help option

  Scenario: node add -h
    When I run ./node add -h
    Then the first line of the help message should be a usage example
    And the help message should include a description of -i and --installer option
    And the help message should include a description of -a and --address option
    And the help message should include a description of -n and --netmask option
    And the help message should include a description of -g and --gateway option
    And the help message should include a description of -m and --mac option
    And the help message should include a description of -w and --wol option
    And the help message should include a description of -t and --trace option
    And the help message should include a description of -v and --verbose option
    And the help message should include a description of -h and --help option
